System: ==== Available Functions ====

Help: --- Available Commands ---
auto all..................: Toggle (on/off): Tee, AutoReply, & AutoExecute
autoreply.................: Toggle real-time prompt analysis (on/off)
autoexe...................: Toggle execution of AI payloads (on/off)
clear.....................: Clear the contents of the AI pane
close history manager.....: Closes the history manager window
close noise manager.......: Closes the noise filter manager window
close policy manager......: Closes the policy manager window
close session manager.....: Closes the session manager window
command line help.........: display all command line options
debug.....................: Toggle debug mode out stderr (on/off)
extended help.............: Display extended help message
features..................: Display new aiterm features
help......................: Display this dynamic help menu
history...................: Display mysql history
hw........................: Display various hardware info
invalidate cache..........: Force a reload of smart cache
list models...............: Display all models from current provider
load config...............: Loads configurations from aiterm.conf
noise filter..............: Toggle noise filter (on/off)
noise add.................: Add a pattern to the noise filter list
noise delete..............: Remove a pattern from the noise filter (TBA)
noise list................: List all active noise filter patterns (TBA)
noise reload..............: Reload noise filters from database
open history manager......: Open History Manager window
open noise manager........: Opens Noise Filter Manager window
open policy manager.......: Open Policy Manager window
open session manager......: Opens the session manager window
save config...............: Saves configuration to aiterm.conf
session default...........: Sets current or specified UUID as default
session delete............: Deletes a session from the database
session description.......: Sets a desctiption to current session
session list..............: Lists sessions stored in database
session load..............: Loads a previous session from database
session new...............: Starts a new AI session
session no default........: Sets no session tto default
session read from global..: Toggle reading from global (on/off)
session show..............: shows the current session uuid and description
session write to global...: Toggle writing to global (on/off)
smart cache...............: Smart Cache Toggle (on/off)
provider..................: Display AI provider [OpenAI/Gemini]
ratelimit.................: Toggle Raate Limiting (on/off)
reset db..................: Reset database connection
reset state...............: Reeset current AI state back to ready
rpm.......................: Set ratelimit Requests Per Minute
status....................: Display operational metrics
tee.......................: Toggle immediate terminal capturing (on/off)
version...................: Display running aiterm version, build ID, and build time
xml tagging...............: Toggle XML Tagging of AI payloads (on/off)


